	<body>
		<section title="XQuery Examples">
        
            <p>The examples here demonstrate eXist's new XQuery
            processing features. XQuery support is still under development. 
            You have to check out the 
            <a href="http://sourceforge.net/cvs/?group_id=17691">latest CVS 
            sources</a> if you want to play with it.</p>
            
            <p>All examples are written in XQuery, using eXist's XQueryGenerator 
            for Cocoon and some XSL stylesheets for display.</p>
            
            <table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="10">
                <tr>
                    <td width="30%" valign="top">
                        <link href="table.xq">Simple Example 1</link>
                    </td>
                    <td width="70%">
                        Prints a table in HTML with 10x10 cells.
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td width="30%" valign="top">
                        <link href="fibo.xq">Fibonacci</link>
                    </td>
                    <td width="70%">
                        Calculates the first 10 Fibonacci numbers.
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td width="30%" valign="top">
                        <link href="functions.xq">Built-in functions</link>
                    </td>
                    <td width="70%">
                        Prints a table showing the signatures of all functions
                        registered within the current XQuery context.
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td width="30%" valign="top">
                        <link href="acronyms.xq">XML Acronyms</link>
                    </td>
                    <td width="70%">
                        Another version of the <a href="http://www.xml-acronym-demystifier.org/">
                        XML Acronym Demystifier</a>, entirely implemented in XQuery.
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            
        </section>
